title: A Pile of Rare Vinyl Comedy Albums
description:
A Pile of Rare Vinyl Comedy Albums. Most are ripped at 128kbps I think, but it&#039;s spoken word, so it doesn&#039;t matter so much. These are old, there are a few pops here and there, but they are all classic comedy. 

This includes:

Allen & Rossi At The Sands

Are You Ready For Phyllis Diller?

George Gobel at The Sands

George Kirby - A Night In Hollywood

Godfrey Cambridge at The Hotel Aladdin

Here&#039;s Milt Kamen!

Jack Paar - The Best of What&#039;s His Name

Jackie "Moms" Mabley at The Playboy Club & Breaks Up the Network

Jimmy Lynch- That Funky Tramp in a Nightclub

Joe E Ross - Should Lesbians Be Allowed to Play Football?

Minnie Pearl - Howdee!

Orson Bean The Hungry I

Robert Klein - Child of the Fifties

Rudy Ray Moore - Sweet Jeeter Peter

Rudy Ray Moore - The Cockpit

Stu Gilliam at the Basin Street West

The Humor Of Rowan and Martin

Tim Conway & Ernie Ghoulardi Anderson - Are We On?

Tim Conway & Ernie Ghoulardi Anderson - Bull


ENJOY. SHARING IS CARING. BE LIKE JOHNNY APPLESEED
